The '''Black Order''' or '''The Black Order of Pan Europa''' are a [[Theistic Satanism|Satanist]] group formerly based in New Zealand. Political scientists [[Jeffrey Kaplan (academic)|Jeffrey Kaplan]] and Leonard Weinberg characterised the Black Order as a "[[Nazism|National Socialist]]-oriented Satanist mail order ministry".{{sfn|Kaplan|Weinberg|1998|p=143}} However, in 1995, the anti-fascist [[Searchlight (magazine)|Searchlight]] organization, following an investigation, described it as part of a functioning international Occult-Fascist Axis.<ref>''David Myatt and the Occult-Fascist Axis'', Searchlight, July 1995.</ref>
{{Infobox organization | name = The Black Order of Pan Europa | named_after = | image = | image_size = | alt = | caption = | logo = | logo_size = | logo_alt = | logo_caption = | abbreviation = | motto = | predecessor = Order of the Left Hand Path | merged = | successor = White Order (schism) | formation = 1994 | founder = [[Kerry Bolton]] | founding_location = New Zealand | extinction = <!-- use {{end date and age|YYYY|MM|DD}} --> | merger = | type = New Religious Movement, Satanism, neo-Nazism, | tax_id = <!-- or | vat_id = (for European organizations) --> | registration_id = <!-- for non-profit org --> | status = | purpose = | headquarters = | location = Australia, England, Ireland, New Zealand, Scandinavia | coords = <!-- {{coord|LAT|LON|display=inline, title}} --> | region = | fields = | membership = | membership_year = | language = | owner = <!-- or | owners = --> | sec_gen = | leader_title = | leader_name = | leader_title2 = | leader_name2 = | leader_title3 = | leader_name3 = | leader_title4 = | leader_name4 = | board_of_directors = | key_people = | main_organ = | parent_organization = | subsidiaries = | secessions = | affiliations = [[Order of Nine Angles]], Ordo Sinistra Vivendi | budget = | budget_year = | revenue = | revenue_year = | disbursements = | expenses = | expenses_year = | endowment = | endowment_year = | staff = | staff_year = | volunteers = | volunteers_year = | website = http://theblackorder.org/ | remarks = | formerly = | footnotes = }}
==Origins== The Black Order was founded in New Zealand by [[Kerry Bolton]] as a successor to his Order of the Left Hand Path.{{sfn|Kaplan|Weinberg|1998|p=143}} Bolton had connections to other neo-Nazi Satanist groups, being the international distributor for the English-based [[Order of Nine Angles]].{{sfn|Goodrick-Clarke|2003|p=229}}
According to Goodrick-Clarke, "in 1994 Bolton set up the Black Order, which claimed a global network of national lodges in Britain, France, Italy, Finland, Sweden, Germany, the United States and Australia, dedicated to fostering National Socialism, fascism, satanism, paganism and other aspects of the European Darkside".{{sfn|Goodrick-Clarke|2003|p=227}} Its quarterly membership bulletin ''The Flaming Sword'' and its successor [[zine]] ''The Nexus'' contained interviews with, among others, [[James Mason (neo-Nazi)|James Mason]], [[George Burdi|George Eric Hawthorne]], Michael Moynihan, [[David Myatt]] and [[Miguel Serrano]], and its articles included studies of Thulianism, Himmler's [[Wewelsburg]], tributes to old SS leaders, "a reprint of the ONA Mass of Heresy [and] contributions from David Myatt on the galactic empire, aeonic strategy and the cosmological magic of National Socialism".{{sfn|Goodrick-Clarke|2003|p=227-228}}
In 1996, a U.S. branch of the Black Order was established.{{sfn|Kaplan|Weinberg|1998|p=143}} In summer that year, they began publication of a magazine, ''Abyss''.{{sfn|Kaplan|Weinberg|1998|p=219}} The U.S. group subsequently fell out with that in New Zealand over the latter's acceptance of homosexual members.{{sfn|Kaplan|Weinberg|1998|p=219}} The U.S. group considered a name change to the White Order as a result of this schism.{{sfn|Kaplan|Weinberg|1998|p=219}}
The name "Black Order" was then adopted by ideologically similar groups around the world which had no formal connection to Bolton's group.{{sfn|Kaplan|Weinberg|1998|p=143}} Kaplan and Weinberg described the Black Order as "a remarkably influential purveyor of National Socialist-oriented occultism throughout the world".{{sfn|Kaplan|Weinberg|1998|p=144}}
In 2016 former members of The Black Order re-established the group with lodges in Australia, England, New Zealand, and Scandinavia. <ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.theblackorder.org/index2.html|title=.:THE BLACK ORDER of Pan Europa:.|website=www.theblackorder.org|access-date=2017-02-16}}</ref>
